            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 3,
            "weighted_score": 0.5669291019439697,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Really fun, chill game.\n\nI got this during a sale for $2.99 and bought about $20 in DLC. Even though its old. this is quite a fun flight simulator. The graphics hold up okay, and there are some mods and DLC that can improve them. Also, there are a ton of free mods that add scenery, planes, and a lot of other stuff. The tutorial missions were actually helpful, and the game plays fine with a X360 gamepad. There are a good number of settings that can increase or reduce the realism and difficulty of the game. The missions are hit and miss, with some being fun and satisfying, others being frustrating but manageable, and yet others being ridiculously hard and tedious. After a while of playing, the game does seem to assume that you know something about flying and will throw out commands such as \"feather the prop\" or \"lean the fuel\"--stuff that's not explained or even mentioned in the tutorials. Anyhow, you can figure out a lot of this stuff through trial and error or looking it up on the internet. \n\nPros:\n+graphics are serviceable\n+real sense of achievement when completing a mission\n+worthwhile and informative tutorials\n+don't need a HOTAS to play\n+lots of free mods and paid DLC to choose from\n+big number of base-game missions\n+really chill and relaxing game \n\nCons: \n-missions vary widely in quality\n-instructions and mission parameters can be vague\n-game sometimes presumes a basic knowledge of aviation\n-most helicopter missions are not fun\n\nAll in all, a real gem, especially if you can get it on sale."
        },
